                <note rend="inline" type="source">551.58B1/56: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-07-16T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 16, 1929—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>74. Your despatch from Geneva, April 20, 1929. Please proceed to Geneva at your
                    early convenience and sign the convention and protocol for the suppression of
                    counterfeiting currency. Do not sign the final act or optional protocol.
                    Telegraph date of signature.</p>
                <p>For your information, in connection with Article 23, this Government proposes
                    that, before the convention is ratified, certain changes in its legislation
                    shall be made.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
